                             Amazon EC2
                             Instance Metadata

   Amazon EC2 provides metadata about your EC2 instances and resources.
   You can use the metadata to configure applications and to monitor your
   resources. The metadata is available as both an HTTP and an HTTPS endpoint.

   For example, you can use the metadata to get information about your
   instances, such as the operating system (OS) running on the instance,
   the Availability Zone, and the instance
